        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>Cepheus is one of the 88 modern constellations, and it lives in the far north of the sky, near Cassiopeia and Polaris.</p>
        <p>In Greek mythology, it represents King Cepheus of <strong>Aethiopia</strong>, husband of Cassiopeia and father of Andromeda.</p>
        <p>It isn’t the brightest constellation, but it has a really satisfying shape as it looks like a simple house/pentagon outline that becomes easy to recognize once you know what you’re looking for.</p>
        <p>It also punches above its weight scientifically. Cepheus includes <strong>Delta Cephei</strong>, the prototype <strong>Cepheid</strong> variable that helped make distance measuring in astronomy possible.</p>
