        <h2>Interesting Stars</h2>
        <p><strong>Alderamin (α Cephei)</strong> is the brightest star in Cepheus. It’s a great starting point for learning the constellation.</p>
        <p><strong>Mu Cephei</strong>, also called the <strong>“Garnet Star”</strong>, is known for its deep red color. It’s a great star to look at using binoculars.</p>
        <p><strong>RW Cephei</strong> is another extreme object. It’s a massive, evolved red supergiant that astronomers watch closely because it is near it's end of life. </p>
        <p>Two more names you might see a lot are <strong>Delta Cephei</strong> (the Cepheid prototype) and <strong>Gamma Cephei (Errai)</strong>, a nearby star system with an exoplanet.</p>
