        <h2>How to Locate?</h2>
        <p>The easiest way in is through <strong>Cassiopeia</strong>. Find the bright “W”, then look nearby for a looser five-star shape that looks like a simple house. That “house” is Cepheus.</p>
        <p>You can also use <strong>Polaris</strong> as a reference point. Cepheus sits in the same general north-sky area.</p>
        <p>Once you’ve got the outline, focus onto <strong>Alderamin (α Cephei)</strong> (the brightest star in the constellation) and explore outward from there.</p>
